# Scene and World
Real land art aerial photography combining Chinese New Year and the Winter Olympics;
Broad snow-covered terrain background;
Strong daylight illumination, clear without vignetting

# Focus and Order
Absolute Subject: A giant red Chinese knot shaped path;
Form of Expression: Giant ink art roughly drawn on the snow;
Visual Logic: The knot structure of the Chinese knot serves as the terrain for human activity, with the tail lines loosening and extending to the bottom of the frame;
Embellishments: Real skiers, performers, and crowds distributed along the path

# Form and Structure
Upper part of the composition: Complex coiled knot loops (similar to text or a maze);
Lower part of the composition: S-shaped winding path lines;
High-altitude overhead aerial view;
Proportional contrast between the massive land art and real human activity

# Material and Language
Main Material: Red pigment drawn on the snow (edges with clear dry brush strokes and texture);
Character Material: Real people wearing bright winter clothing (ski gear, dragon/lion dance props);
Ground Details: Real texture of accumulated snow and clear ski/footprint marks;
Bottom features a black running script calligraphy title “{argument name="title" default="2026 Let's Go Together"}”

# Source of Tension
“Flat snow painting” carrying “real three-dimensional movement”;
Combination of the traditional symbol of the Chinese knot and modern actions of skiing/celebration;
Visual contrast between the grand, rough land texture and the delicate human activity

